About Me

I am originally from Waldwick, NJ, a small suburban town with a tight-knit community. After living there for my entire life, I came to realize that suburban life is not for me; I need the noise and activity of a city in my life.

I came to MIT with a strong interest in leadership, which as only grown over the last four years. I'm heavily involved in my sorority, Kappa Alpha Theta, my dorm government in Baker House, and Four Consulting, a student-run consulting club on campus.

In my free time, I enjoy attending concerts in Boston/Cambridge, going to coffeeshops in the area, and watching television and movies.
